SMILING JUST BY LOOKING AT HIM.

188
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:02,125
- START SMILING?

189
00:14:02,875 --> 00:14:05,083
I START TO SMILE?

190
00:14:05,166 --> 00:14:06,541
- YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

191
00:14:06,625 --> 00:14:07,875
NOW AS FOR ME,

192
00:14:07,958 --> 00:14:10,500
IT'S TRUE THAT I REALLY
LIKE DOGGIE'S PRETTY FACE,

193
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:12,750
BUT MORE THAN THAT,
HE'S SO PATHETIC

194
00:14:12,833 --> 00:14:14,083
THAT WHEN I WATCH HIM,

195
00:14:14,166 --> 00:14:18,083
I JUST WANT TO SCOOP HIM UP
AND HELP HIM ALONG.

196
00:14:18,166 --> 00:14:20,958
I'M SORRY, I'M DOING
ALL OF THE TALKING HERE.

197
00:14:21,583 --> 00:14:22,833
WELL, GOT TO GO.

198
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:26,833
- TO RENTON.
- HUH?

199
00:14:26,916 --> 00:14:30,208
- I WANT TO TALK TO RENTON
ABOUT ALL SORTS OF THINGS.

200
00:14:30,291 --> 00:14:32,958
BUT, RIGHT NOW, I'M AFRAID
TO EVEN LOOK AT HIS FACE.

201
00:14:33,791 --> 00:14:35,083
I WONDER WHY?

202
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:37,333
- (sighs )

203
00:14:37,958 --> 00:14:39,666
- YOU KNOW WHAT, EUREKA,

204
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:41,750
YOU BETTER CURB
THAT NAIVETY OF YOURS

205
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,500
OR THE OTHER GIRLS
WILL HATE YOU.

206
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:46,208
I MEAN, IT'S ALL BECAUSE
YOU'RE IN LOVE.

207
00:14:46,291 --> 00:14:48,916
- LOVE?
- YEAH, IN LOVE.

208
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:58,875
- Renton: AMAZING! YOU GUYS
REALLY KEEP IT NEAT.

209
00:14:58,958 --> 00:15:00,291
- Ray: THANK YOU.

210
00:15:00,375 --> 00:15:03,291
- THIS IS SUCH A BIG DIFFERENCE
FROM THAT OTHER SHIP.

211
00:15:03,375 --> 00:15:05,375
- IF IT'S A COMPLIMENT,
IT'S UNNECESSARY.

212
00:15:05,458 --> 00:15:07,166
- NO, THAT'S ISN'T WHAT I MEANT.

213
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:09,000
- HEY, KIDS WILL BE KIDS.

214
00:15:09,083 --> 00:15:11,750
DON'T WORRY ABOUT BEING
SO CONSIDERATE OF ADULTS.

215
00:15:11,833 --> 00:15:13,750
YOU CAN ONLY BE
A KID FOR SO LONG,

216
00:15:13,833 --> 00:15:15,958
SO YOU MIGHT AS WELL ENJOY IT.

217
00:15:16,041 --> 00:15:19,541
- IN THE END, I TOOK FULL
ADVANTAGE OF WHAT HE SAID TO ME.

218
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:22,791
IF THAT TECTONIC SHIFT
HADN'T OCCURRED,

219
00:15:22,875 --> 00:15:24,208
MAYBE I WOULDN'T
HAVE BEEN ABLE TO

220
00:15:24,291 --> 00:15:26,750
AVAIL MYSELF OF THEIR OFFER.

221
00:15:42,375 --> 00:15:45,041
- Charles: I WON'T GIVE YOU ANY.
THEY'RE ALL MINE.

222
00:15:45,125 --> 00:15:46,250
- HUH?

223
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:47,875
- SORRY, I WAS STARING.

224
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:49,791
DID YOU START RIDING RECENTLY?

225
00:15:49,875 --> 00:15:52,750
- HEY, I WAS BORN WITH
A BOARD ATTACHED TO MY FEET.

226
00:15:53,166 --> 00:15:54,583
- BUT...

227
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:56,291
YOU CAN'T MAKE REALLY
QUICK MANEUVERS

228
00:15:56,375 --> 00:15:57,666
WITH THE BOARD MADE LIKE THIS.

229
00:15:57,750 --> 00:15:58,916
THE WHEEL'S PRETTY BIG,

